## 3. Frontend Audit (Flutter)

### ✅ What's Working Well

| Item | Detail |
|------|--------|
| **ApiService** | Singleton, auto token refresh on 401, dedup of parallel refresh calls, 10s request timeout, cert pinning on production domain |
| **Certificate Pinning** | SHA-256 fingerprint enforced against `api.fraudshieldprotect.com`, skipped for dev |
| **Token refresh** | [refreshToken()](file:///c:/Fraudshield/fraudshield/lib/services/api_service.dart#109-124) properly deduplicates concurrent calls via `_refreshFuture` |
| **Screen coverage** | 43 screens, 26 widgets — full feature surface covered |
| **Crashlytics** | Integrated (Feb 24), crashes stream to Firebase console |
| **Voice Detection** | Correctly hidden behind "Coming Soon" |
| **Transaction categories** | PHONE/BANK/DOC correctly passed as `checkType` |
| **Recent checks** | [recent_checks_service.dart](file:///c:/Fraudshield/fraudshield/lib/services/recent_checks_service.dart) implemented |
| **PDPA** | Privacy policy, ToS, consent, data export all present |

### ⚠️ Issues Found

| Severity | ID | Finding | File | Fix |
|:--------:|-----|---------|------|-----|
| 🟠 | F1 | **Tokens stored in `SharedPreferences`** (plain text) — [_setTokens()](file:///c:/Fraudshield/fraudshield/lib/services/api_service.dart#41-56) uses `prefs.setString('auth_token')`. This is insecure on rooted/jailbroken devices | `lib/services/api_service.dart:44,50` | Migrate to `flutter_secure_storage` — the package is already listed in roadmap (M4), ~1 hr |
| 🟠 | F2 | **`static const bool _isAndroidEmulator = true`** hardcoded — this flag has no bearing on current code but could cause subtle bugs if it's referenced in future | `lib/services/api_service.dart:13` | Change to `kDebugMode` or remove |
| 🟠 | F3 | **Email verification not enforced** — backend `S7` is not implemented, user can use app without verifying email | Backend | Implement real email (B1) then wire OTP verification screen |
| 🟡 | F4 | **`debugPrint` calls remain in production builds** — [ApiService](file:///c:/Fraudshield/fraudshield/lib/services/api_service.dart#10-704) has many `debugPrint` guarded by `kDebugMode` (good), but other screens may not | Various screens | Audit all screen files for bare `print()` calls |
| 🟡 | F5 | **No app version / force-update check** — old clients can hit deprecated API shapes | — | Add version check on app startup |
| 🟡 | F6 | **No Bahasa Malaysia localization** | — | Add `flutter_localizations` + `intl` |
| 🟡 | F7 | **[test_screen.dart](file:///c:/Fraudshield/fraudshield/lib/screens/test_screen.dart) (4.5 KB) present in production screens folder** | [lib/screens/test_screen.dart](file:///c:/Fraudshield/fraudshield/lib/screens/test_screen.dart) | Remove or exclude from release builds |
| 🟡 | F8 | **[transaction_screen.dart](file:///c:/Fraudshield/fraudshield/lib/screens/transaction_screen.dart) is 0 bytes (empty file)** | [lib/screens/transaction_screen.dart](file:///c:/Fraudshield/fraudshield/lib/screens/transaction_screen.dart) | Delete or implement |
| 🟡 | F9 | **Google Sign-In hang** — last session (Feb 24) left this unresolved. Backend `/auth/google` route exists | [lib/screens/login_screen.dart](file:///c:/Fraudshield/fraudshield/lib/screens/login_screen.dart) | Debug and fix (see conversation 1d82a697) |

